-- Enemy paths, one row per polyline point, in map (image-pixel) space matching
-- the level art. point_index is travel order: point 0 is the spawn, the last is
-- the exit.
--
-- Lexington and Concord (path 0): the British advance -- enters at "To Boston"
-- (right), follows the road west through the S-curve past Lexington Green, up to
-- Concord, and out across the Old North Bridge (left). Hand-traced route,
-- centered on the road via a distance-transform ridge with the tower-slot
-- platforms excluded, smoothed with a centripetal Catmull-Rom spline and
-- arc-length resampled to evenly spaced points (~1.4px apart) for smooth enemy
-- walking. Traced from images/lexington_and_concord.png.
